HI @kramasamy 
- 1. compile and install thrift 0.9.3 and use `which thrift` eg `/usr/local/bin/thrift` to generate java code , 
  but this consumes too much time on compiling thrift;
- 2.use thrift executables like `third_party/thrift/thrift-linux-x86_64.exe` to generate code at runtime , but this may  not proper  run on all linux-dist platforms;

So why don't we :
- 3. do not generate code at compile time , just use thrift 0.9.3 to generate java code locally, and use generated java code directlly?
